[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/a_few_days.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
A few days later. Art Week continues, transformed by what happened.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_afternoon_sun.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
The afternoon sun casts long shadows across the courtyard. Students mill about, their conversations softer than before.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/The_spots.mp3" volume="0.0"]
The spot where "The Reader" once stood now holds something new.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	join Celestine (animated) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: Hey, what's that? Where Mia's sculpture used to be?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_approaches.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist approaches the pedestal, curious.
else:
	join Conrad (half) left
	join Mark (Mark_half) right
	Mark: Hey, what's that? Where Mia's sculpture used to be?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_approaches.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist approaches the pedestal, curious.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/a_collaborative_piece.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
A collaborative piece stands in place of the broken sculpture.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/dozens_of_small.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
Dozens of small clay hands, each made by a different student, reach upward together, holding an open book.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/a_plaque_reads.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
A plaque reads\: "Together We Rise - A collaborative tribute to The Reader."
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: The art club made this. Each student contributed a hand.
	Mark: Wait, even Victor?
	Celestine: Even Victor. His is the one in the center, holding the book's spine.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/mark_examines_the.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Mark examines the piece more closely.
	Mark: That's... actually kind of beautiful. From destruction, something new.
	Celestine: Mia said art is about sharing. Looks like everyone learned that lesson.
	Celestine: Even Victor.
else:
	Conrad: The art club made this. Each student contributed a hand.
	Mark: Wait, even Victor?
	Conrad: Even Victor. His is the one in the center, holding the book's spine.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/mark_examines_the.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Mark examines the piece more closely.
	Mark: That's... actually kind of beautiful. From destruction, something new.
	Conrad: Mia said art is about sharing. Looks like everyone learned that lesson.
	Conrad: Even Victor.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/they_stand_in.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
They stand in comfortable silence, admiring the collaborative piece.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_afternoon_breeze.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
The afternoon breeze rustles through the courtyard.
Mark: Hey, what's that?
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/mark_points_to.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
He points to something tucked behind the pedestal, partially hidden by shadow.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_reaches.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist reaches down and pulls out a small, elegant card.
else:
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_reaches.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist reaches down and pulls out a small, elegant card.
[signal arg="unlock_evidence bc_card_creativity_c3"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_paper_is.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
The paper is thick and cream-colored, the handwriting precise and old-fashioned.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: Another one.
	Mark: B.C. again?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_nods.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist nods, their expression growing serious.
	Celestine: "Lesson 3\: Creativity."
	Celestine: "True artists create to express, not to compete."
	Celestine: "Envy sees another's light and tries to extinguish it..."
	Celestine: "...not realizing it could have warmed them both."
	Mark: That's... exactly what happened with Victor.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_continues.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist continues reading.
	Celestine: "The jealous heart destroys what it cannot possess."
	Celestine: "The wise heart learns to admire what it cannot be."
else:
	Conrad: Another one.
	Mark: B.C. again?
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_nods.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist nods, their expression growing serious.
	Conrad: "Lesson 3\: Creativity."
	Conrad: "True artists create to express, not to compete."
	Conrad: "Envy sees another's light and tries to extinguish it..."
	Conrad: "...not realizing it could have warmed them both."
	Mark: That's... exactly what happened with Victor.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_continues.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist continues reading.
	Conrad: "The jealous heart destroys what it cannot possess."
	Conrad: "The wise heart learns to admire what it cannot be."
Mark: Three cases. Three lessons. Three cards.
Mark: Truth, from the exam sabotage. Responsibility, from the missing fund.
Mark: And now Creativity.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: Someone's teaching us. Through these mysteries.
else:
	Conrad: Someone's teaching us. Through these mysteries.
Mark: But who? And how do they know about these cases before we solve them?
join "Diwata Laya" (Half_mirror) center
[signal arg="laya_start"]
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/diwata_laya_appears.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
"Diwata Laya" appears, her eyes fixed on the card with unusual intensity.
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]B.C. Their presence grows stronger with each lesson.[/color][/i]
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]They are not merely watching. They are guiding.[/color][/i]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	"Celestine (Thinking)": Guiding us toward what?
else:
	"Conrad (Thinking)": Guiding us toward what?
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]I cannot see the end. Only the path unfolding before us.[/color][/i]
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]But each lesson builds on the last. Truth. Responsibility. Creativity.[/color][/i]
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]These are not random values. They form something larger.[/color][/i]
Mark: A curriculum? Like someone's training us?
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Perhaps. Or a test. Preparing you for something to come.[/color][/i]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	"Celestine (Thinking)": Who is B.C.? Can you sense anything about them?
else:
	"Conrad (Thinking)": Who is B.C.? Can you sense anything about them?
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/diwata_laya_shakes.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
"Diwata Laya" shakes her head slowly, her form flickering.
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Even I cannot pierce that veil. They exist... outside my sight.[/color][/i]
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]Older than my awareness. Patient beyond measure.[/color][/i]
"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]But I sense no malice. Only purpose. Ancient and patient.[/color][/i]
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	"Celestine (Thinking)": That's both reassuring and terrifying.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]The cards will continue, Celestine. The lessons will grow harder.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]But you are growing too. Stronger. Wiser. More attuned to truth.[/color][/i]
	[signal arg="laya_end"]
	leave "Diwata Laya"
	Mark: A mysterious teacher who leaves cryptic cards after we solve crimes.
	Mark: Our lives have gotten really weird since you found Laya, sis.
else:
	"Conrad (Thinking)": That's both reassuring and terrifying.
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]The cards will continue, Conrad. The lessons will grow harder.[/color][/i]
	"Diwata Laya": [i][color=#9999ff]But you are growing too. Stronger. Wiser. More attuned to truth.[/color][/i]
	[signal arg="laya_end"]
	leave "Diwata Laya"
	Mark: A mysterious teacher who leaves cryptic cards after we solve crimes.
	Mark: Our lives have gotten really weird since you found Laya, Conrad.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: Weird, but meaningful.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_looks.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist looks at the collaborative sculpture, then back at the B.C. card.
	Celestine: Victor wanted to be seen. To matter.
	Celestine: But he was looking for validation in the wrong places.
	Celestine: Competition pushed him to improve. But when it became about tearing others down...
	Mark: That's when it stopped being about the art.
	Celestine: Exactly. Creation should lift people up. Not tear them down.
	Celestine: Victor had real skill. He just forgot why he started making art in the first place.
else:
	Conrad: Weird, but meaningful.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/the_protagonist_looks.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	The protagonist looks at the collaborative sculpture, then back at the B.C. card.
	Conrad: Victor wanted to be seen. To matter.
	Conrad: But he was looking for validation in the wrong places.
	Conrad: Competition pushed him to improve. But when it became about tearing others down...
	Mark: That's when it stopped being about the art.
	Conrad: Exactly. Creation should lift people up. Not tear them down.
	Conrad: Victor had real skill. He just forgot why he started making art in the first place.
Mark: And Mia?
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: She never forgot. That's why her work resonates.
	Celestine: It's not about technique. It's about connection. About heart.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/mark_stretches_looking.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Mark stretches, looking at the setting sun painting the sky in oranges and purples.
	Mark: Three cases solved. Three mysterious cards collected.
	Mark: Think there'll be more?
	Celestine: "The chain continues." That's what B.C. wrote on the first card.
	Celestine: There will definitely be more.
	Mark: Then we'll be ready.
	Celestine: Together.
else:
	Conrad: She never forgot. That's why her work resonates.
	Conrad: It's not about technique. It's about connection. About heart.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/mark_stretches_looking.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	Mark stretches, looking at the setting sun painting the sky in oranges and purples.
	Mark: Three cases solved. Three mysterious cards collected.
	Mark: Think there'll be more?
	Conrad: "The chain continues." That's what B.C. wrote on the first card.
	Conrad: There will definitely be more.
	Mark: Then we'll be ready.
	Conrad: Together.
[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/they_share_a.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
They share a smile - the easy, comfortable kind that comes from facing challenges side by side.
Mark: Come on. Let's get some food. All this detective work makes me hungry.
if {selected_character} == "celestine":
	Celestine: Everything makes you hungry, Mark.
	Mark: Fair point. But also, I'm right.
	[voice path="res://assets/audio/voice/Chapter 3/c3s6/they_walk_away.mp3" volume="0.0" bus="Voice"]
	They walk away from the courtyard, leaving the collaborative sculpture glowing in the afternoon light.
